** Civil/Structural Technical Sales Engineer, **

** Responsible for ANZ **

Leviat, a CRH company, is a global leader in connecting, fixing, lifting and
anchoring technology for the construction industry. Leviat’s engineered
products and innovative construction solutions are used in a variety of
sectors from residential to infrastructure, enabling our customers to build
better, stronger, safer and faster. Leviat employs almost 3,000 people at 60
locations across North America, Europe and Asia-Pacific. Pursuing ambitious
growth plans, Leviat offers excellent long-term career development
opportunities.

** Position Overview **

** Technical Sales Engineer ** , 

As a ** Technical Sales Engineer ** you will be a part of the technical sales
team providing support to both the commercial and operational functions to
deliver best in class customer service and product. Working locally but as
part of a much larger Global Marketing Communications team, this role requires
you to liaise and network with a broad range of stakeholders. This role works
closely with the National Pre-Sales Manager to develop and implement growth
strategies and ensure that these are in line with the long-term Leviat goals.

The role will suit a self-motivated, and confident individual who is
experienced in delivering technical strategies to meet organisational
objectives. A creative and lateral thinking individual who works cooperatively
with colleagues to effectively provide technical expertise and deliver
relevant solutions to the customer base.

** Job description **

The Technical Support Specialist plays a vital role in ensuring the success of
construction projects by providing both pro-active and re-active technical
support to stakeholders.

The role includes:

  * Promoting engineered construction solutions to external stakeholders during conferences, trade shows and sponsored events. 
  * Organising & conducting technical seminars / webinars to engineers, architects & consultants. 
  * Undertaking technical & site enquiries to resolve projects’ design issues and educating specifiers the recommended application & installation of Leviat range of products. 
  * Providing support to sales activities, including managing EOI’s, tenders and product testing & approvals for major projects. 
  * Collaborating with other departments within the organisation to provide technical solutions. 
  * Develop and implement growth strategies, in line with Leviat objectives. 
  * Build and maintain positive internal and external customer relationships. 
  * Analyse and explore market trends, identifying new opportunities / risk analysis, and potential income streams / acquisitions. 

** Essential requirements **

  * Excellent written and verbal communication skills. 
  * Team player with the ability to contribute both individually and as part of a team. 
  * Self-confidence with strong interpersonal skills, an excellent communicator with the ability to liaise with people at all levels. 
  * Flexibility and ability to multitask. 
  * Self-motivated with a “hands on” results driven approach. 
  * Strong systems skills with advanced proficiency in Microsoft Office and AutoCAD 
  * Minimum degree qualified in structural engineering or similar. 
  * Excellent verbal and written communication with a willingness to learn and develop others around you. 

** Desirable requirements **

  * Experience in delivery of detailed design is highly desirable. 
  * Showcase your strong internal and external stakeholder management experience, a can-do attitude and importantly a strong team player who works well in an agile and collaborative environment. 
  * Demonstrates deep industry knowledge and expertise in area of specialism; deepening experience in dealing with complex technical issues. 

** You will also have access to: **

  * Flexible work (per Hybrid Work Policy) 
  * On-site parking 
  * Annual Flu Vaccination Program 
  * Employee Assistance Program 

** Personal Attributes **

Team Player | Hands-on | Proactive | Personable | Resilient | Flexible
|Organised | Accountable| Sense of Humour & Positivity.

** About Leviat **

Our trusted product brands, including Ancon, HALFEN, Isedio, Connolly and
Helifix, are all known for high performance, quality and reliability.

We help our ambitious construction partners to turn architectural visions into
reality and our engineers provide technical design assistance at every stage
of a project, from initial planning to installation and beyond. Our technical
support services range from simple product selection through to the
development of a fully customised project-specific design solution. Our
digital engineering tools include industry-leading calculation and design
software and BIM objects.

Every promise we make locally, has the commitment and dedication of our global
team behind it.

